This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with image generation. The use of variational inference also suggests that it may belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) sub-category. Additionally, the paper involves the use of conditional GANs, which are commonly used in the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. The paper may also belong to the graphics (cs.GR) sub-category as it deals with image generation and the improvement of generation quality and diversity. Finally, the use of experimental results suggests that the paper may belong to the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category.
